# **B2B CMO Club Internal Community AI**

## **Feature Plan \+ Priority Backlog (P0–P3) — v2 (AI‑First, Intake‑Driven, Internal‑Only)**

**This document is the build‑ready feature plan for the B2B CMO Club Internal Community AI.**

---

## **1\) Executive summary**

### **1.1 What we are building**

An internal‑only **Retention Intelligence \+ Concierge Enablement Engine** that powers the B2B CMO Club’s “white‑glove concierge” experience at **fixed cost** (one community manager).

This AI will:

* Maintain a continuously updated, evidence‑backed “truth profile” for every member.  
* Detect opportunities and risks using **two engines**:  
  1. **Live signals** (Slack \+ LinkedIn \+ careers pages)  
  2. **Forced‑success signals** (intake \+ surveys \+ mastermind calls \+ internal knowledge) surveys sent via slack (we can use our own platform and have a public endpoint for surveys)  
* Convert signals into **ranked actions** (primarily drafted Slack DMs from the Community Manager account).  
* Run a weekly “value guarantee” system (minimum one value drop/member/week).  
* Enable programming (masterminds \+ workshops \+ speakers) using data intersections across members.

### **1.2 Why this will be good**

B2B’s AI will perform well because the club is structurally designed for AI performance:

* **Complete intake completeness** via the closer intake call (high‑integrity structured data).  
* **Identity stitching solved upfront** (emails used for Slack/Zoom/etc.).  
* **Internal‑only action cockpit \+ auto‑send logic** (CM efficiency).  
* **Weekly forced‑success engine** (not monthly).  
* **LinkedIn \+ careers page live signals** on a scheduled 12‑hour loop.  
* **Hard outcome loops** (1–10 ratings \+ feedback \<6) to train the system over time.

---

## **2\) Core objective and KPI contract**

### **2.1 Core objective (non‑negotiable)**

The AI’s job is **not just support**. It is a **Retention Intelligence \+ Concierge Enablement Engine**.

### **2.2 Primary KPIs the AI must influence**

* Renewal rate  
* Expansion/adoption (Slack, masterminds, workshops; app later if ever)  
* Time‑to‑value for new members  
* Perceived “they really know me” factor  
* Value delivered to members (wins, intros, savings, solved problems)

---

## **3\) Phase 1 scope constraints (locked decisions)**

### **3.1 AI is internal‑only (Phase 1\)**

* No member‑facing chatbot yet.  
* Community team uses:  
  * Dashboard (Next.js/Vercel)  
  * Internal AI chat inside dashboard  
  * Slack admin notifications

### **3.2 Messaging mechanics (Slack)**

* Proactive outreach goes out as the **Community Manager’s Slack account**, AI drafted.  
* Auto‑send is allowed **for any outreach type** (intros/perks/resources/invites/check‑ins) **only when**:  
  1. The member replied to the last CM message **or** the previous conversation is marked “closed”, and  
  2. **24+ hours** have passed since the last message in that DM thread.  
* No hard “max DM frequency”—the response‑gating prevents double‑sending and spam.

### **3.3 Forced success cadence (weekly)**

* Minimum **one value drop per member per week**  
* Preferred forced‑success order:  
  1. Intros  
  2. Perks  
  3. Resources  
  4. Workshop invite  
  5. Check‑in question

### **3.4 Masterminds and workshops cadence**

* Masterminds: **1 mastermind per \~5 members**, self‑hosted; AI suggests intersection topics. (Group stability policy remains: group stays the same; members can request changes.)  
* Workshops/speaker events: **2–4 per month** (bi‑weekly to weekly).

### **3.5 Transcript provider and canonical system**

* Transcripts: Recall.ai (via custom tool)  
* Canonical CRM/source of truth: Supabase \+ Prisma  
* Membership/payments: Supabase \+ Stripe integration

---

## **4\) Data sources & ingestion spec (what the AI learns from)**

### **4.1 Structured “truth sources” (highest priority)**

These are the sources designed to minimize hallucinations:

1. Closer intake call recording \+ transcript (deep capture)  
2. Intake structured form/fields (completed during/after call)  
3. Member profile confirmation message (“what’s wrong/missing?”) — creates verified facts  
4. Surveys (monthly/quarterly refresh, as defined below) survey sent via slack (we can use our own platform and have a public endpoint for surveys)

### **4.2 Ongoing internal signals**

5. Slack channels (messages, threads, reactions)

**Slack channel structure (AI signal design)**

* **Core channels (auto-join / Tier 1):**  
  * \#announcements (read-only updates)  
  * \#introductions (templated intro required)  
  * \#wins (pinned template/instructions for wins; speaker sourcing)   
  * \#asks (pinned template/instructions for asks; highest-signal requests)  
  * \#problem-solving (tactical help / troubleshooting)  
  * \#tech-stack (tools; perks matching)  
  * \#marketing-tactics (general tactics \+ discussion)  
  * \#hiring-and-people (hiring, team, operators)  
  * \#partnership-opportunities (co-marketing/JVs)  
  * \#perks (perk hub \+ new perk notifications)  
  * \#market-signals (curated weekly prompts/signals)  
  * \#build-in-public (experiments \+ learnings)  
  * \#general (light; discourage tactical asks here)  
  * \#cold-email, \#cold-text, \#seo, \#ppc, \#social-media-management, \#social-media-advertising, etc.  
  * \#mastermind- (self-hosted; \~5 members)  
  * \#velocity (high-standards program)

Slack ingestion must capture messages, threads, and reactions across these channels (respecting membership and privacy rules).

6. Mastermind calls (single main room; whole transcript usable)  
7. Accountability pod posts (monthly goals \+ receipts)  
8. CourseCreator360 / internal knowledge corpus

---

## **4.3 Live external signals (12-hour cadence)**

**Goal:** capture high-value external signals without ingesting excessive content.

In addition to LinkedIn and company careers pages, the AI will also monitor:

* **Instagram (company \+ personal profiles)**  
* **Indeed (job postings and role changes)**  
* **X (Twitter) profiles (company \+ personal)**

All external signals are **public-only** and do **not** require member logins.

---

### **4.3.1 LinkedIn monitoring targets (public-only)**

* Member personal posts (public)  
* Company page posts (public)  
* Job changes (when observable from public profile deltas or announcements)  
* Hiring announcements (LinkedIn job posts if public, plus company careers page changes)

No logins are required from members (public signal collection only).

---

### **4.3.2 Instagram monitoring targets (public-only)**

* Company Instagram posts and bio changes  
* Member personal Instagram posts (if public and provided at intake)  
* Signals such as:  
  * product or campaign launches  
  * brand repositioning  
  * hiring announcements  
  * major engagement spikes  
  * link-in-bio or CTA changes

---

### **4.3.3 Indeed monitoring targets (public-only)**

* New job postings associated with the member’s company  
* Changes in role types or hiring volume over time  
* Signals such as:  
  * team expansion  
  * function prioritization (e.g., lifecycle, RevOps, paid media)  
  * mismatch between stated goals and hiring behavior

---

### **4.3.4 X (Twitter) monitoring targets (public-only)**

* Member personal X profile activity (if public and provided)  
* Company X profile activity  
* Signals such as:  
  * strategic opinions or market commentary  
  * expressed frustration or urgency  
  * reactions to competitors or industry changes  
  * early signals of experimentation or pivots

---

### **4.3.5 Careers page monitoring**

* For each member company, store a canonical careers page URL at intake (or derive from company site)  
* Monitor for changes and new job postings  
* Treat the most recent changes as highest value

---

### **4.3.6 “Post analysis” summarization layer (anti-bloat)**

For every detected LinkedIn, Instagram, Indeed, X, or careers-page item:

Run a lightweight analysis prompt to extract:

* **“What happened?”** (one sentence)  
* **Tags** (hiring, launch, pivot, messaging, product update, funding, partnership, thought leadership)  
* **Implied needs/opportunities**  
* **Recommended action type(s)** (intro / perk / resource / workshop invite / check-in)

Store:

* Link to original source  
* Timestamp  
* Structured summary \+ tags (not full raw content unless needed for audit)

Add the summary into the member’s context feed.

---

## **5\) System architecture (internal components)**

### **5.1 Canonical “Truth Graph” (Supabase \+ Prisma)**

The AI is built on a member truth graph:

* **Facts**: goals, bottlenecks, stack tools, constraints, initiatives, hiring plans, expertise  
* **Signals**: Slack events, call highlights, LinkedIn/careers summaries  
* **Actions**: recommendations, message drafts, intros, perk sends  
* **Outcomes**: 1–10 ratings \+ conditional feedback (\<6) \+ escalation

Every fact must have provenance:

* source\_type (intake, survey, slack, mastermind, linkedin, careers)  
* source\_id (call id, slack message id, linkedin signal id)  
* timestamp  
* confidence

### **5.2 Opportunity pipeline (“Signal → Action”)**

All incoming data becomes standardized **Opportunity Items**:

* type: hiring, pain signal, win, topic trend, tool mention, partnership request, etc.  
* urgency score  
* relevance to member’s goals  
* recommended next actions

Opportunity Items are converted into:

* recommendations  
* message drafts  
* tasks in the dashboard queues

### **5.3 Concierge Command Center (dashboard)**

The dashboard is the operating surface for one CM:

* Member profile view (“truth profile \+ current context \+ actions”)  
* Who needs attention list  
* Opportunity feed  
* Draft messages queue (manual send / approve auto-send)  
* Intros queue \+ outcomes  
* Perks queue \+ outcomes  
* Weekly forced-success queue  
* Programming planner (masterminds \+ workshop topics \+ speakers)

### **5.4 Internal AI Chat (in-dashboard)**

The CM/founders can ask:

* “Who should I talk to this week?”  
* “What matters to \[Member\] right now?”  
* “Draft a DM to \[Member\] about \[X\] using evidence.”  
* “Which 5 members should be spotlighted for a workshop on \[topic\]?”

---

# **6\) Feature plan \+ priority backlog (P0–P3)**

**Note on priorities:** The Sora Media AI spec is largely P0 in spirit (core concierge \+ retention engine). B2B keeps those as P0 and adds additional P0 items enabled by high-quality intake and the club’s AI-first design.

---

## **P0 — Launch-critical (must ship before public scale)**

### **P0.0 Intake Completeness \+ Identity Stitching (the B2B advantage)**

**What:** a structured intake system that produces verified, high-integrity member data so the AI can be precise from Day 1\.

**Includes:**

* **Closer intake call script \+ structured form** (goals, bottlenecks, constraints, stack by category, hiring plans, expertise, preferences).  
* **Completeness gate:** a member cannot be marked “Active” until required fields are captured.  
* **Identity stitching:** capture and link all identities at intake:  
  * primary email  
  * secondary email(s)  
  * Slack email (if different)  
  * Zoom email (if different)  
  * assistant/EA email (optional)  
* **Member verification loop:** after intake, send “Member Truth Profile v1” for corrections; store edits as verified facts.

**Outputs:**

* verified Member Truth Profile (with provenance)  
* stable identity mapping (Slack user ↔ member)

**Acceptance criteria:**

* intake completeness is enforced programmatically (no “best effort”); missing required fields block onboarding automations  
* member corrections update the truth graph and reduce future wrong recommendations

---

### **P0.1 Truth Graph \+ Provenance Storage (Supabase/Prisma)**

**What:** canonical schema for member facts \+ signals \+ actions \+ outcomes.  
**Inputs:** intake transcript \+ structured fields \+ Slack \+ surveys \+ masterminds \+ LinkedIn/careers summaries.  
**Outputs:** queryable profile facts with sources \+ timestamps \+ confidence.  
**Acceptance criteria:** every fact displayed to CM has provenance; system supports “this is wrong” corrections.

---

### **P0.2 Ingestion: Slack (messages \+ threads \+ reactions)**

**What:** capture all Slack activity from Tier-1 channels \+ opted-in Tier-2 channels.  
**Outputs:** searchable log, embeddings, tags for \[ASK\]/\[WIN\]/\[HIRING\] templates.  
**Acceptance:** near-real-time ingestion; stable mapping of slack user → member identity.

---

### **P0.3 Ingestion: Calls (Recall.ai transcripts for intake \+ masterminds)**

**What:** ingest recordings/transcripts and chunk into retrievable units.  
**Outputs:** structured highlights \+ embeddings; update member truth graph.  
**Acceptance:** intake calls reliably produce structured facts; masterminds generate topic signals.

---

### **P0.4 Ingestion: Surveys (refresh engine)**

**What:** scheduled surveys that update truth facts (goals, stack changes, hiring plans).  
**Cadence:** monthly “quick refresh” \+ quarterly “deep refresh” (implementation detail).  
**Acceptance:** survey updates create new fact versions with timestamps; old facts remain viewable.

surveys sent via slack (we can use our own platform and have a public endpoint for surveys)

---

### **P0.5 Ingestion: Knowledge corpus (CourseCreator360 \+ club policies)**

**What:** index internal knowledge for retrieval and recommendation.  
**Acceptance:** AI can attach 1–3 relevant resources to a member’s current bottleneck.

---

### **P0.6 Live External Signal Harvester (LinkedIn \+ Careers) — 12-hour loop**

**What:** every 12 hours per member, gather public LinkedIn \+ careers signals.  
**Key constraints (locked):**

* public-only (no member logins)  
* do post/careers item analysis summary (avoid content bloat)  
* recency-weighted scoring

**Outputs:**

* LinkedInSignal / CareerSignal objects  
* “What happened?” summaries \+ tags  
* Opportunity items \+ recommended actions

**Acceptance:**

* each member gets a refresh at least every 12 hours  
* system stores summary \+ link, not raw dumps  
* new job postings trigger opportunity items

---

### **P0.7 Member Truth Profile 2.0 (Unified Intelligence Profile — B2B version)**

**What:** single pane of glass for each member.  
**Must include** (Sora Media baseline \+ B2B additions):

* company snapshot (industry, revenue band, growth stage)  
* goals (ranked)  
* bottlenecks (ranked)  
* emotional state trend (burnout/excitement/frustration)  
* engagement velocity / trend (if possible)  
* stack by category \+ notes  
* hiring plans  
* expertise (“can help with”) \+ proof links  
* last 10 meaningful signals (Slack \+ LinkedIn \+ calls)  
* recommended next actions (ranked) \+ why \+ evidence

**Acceptance:** profile page loads fast; evidence links are clickable; CM can edit/correct.

---

### **P0.8 Concierge Briefing Agent (pre-interaction)**

**What:** generate a 90-second briefing before any DM/check-in/renewal convo.  
**Outputs:** “what matters now,” “what not to say,” “next action,” risk snapshot.  
**Acceptance:** one-click from member profile; references evidence.

---

### **P0.9 Attention Radar (Who Needs Attention \+ Risk Scoring \+ Playbooks)**

**What:** proactive relationship ops view: “who to talk to this week.”  
**Signals:** Slack drop, missed calls, sentiment drift, reduced peer interactions.  
**Outputs:** ranked list \+ reason \+ recommended playbook \+ drafted DM.  
**Acceptance:** CM can sort/filter by risk, renewal window, inactivity.

---

### **P0.10 Opportunity-to-Action Engine (Live \+ Forced Success)**

**What:** detect leverage points and produce actions.  
**Live triggers (examples):**

* member posts about a problem on Slack  
* member posts on LinkedIn about hiring/launch/issue  
* careers page update indicates hiring  
  **Forced-success triggers:**  
* weekly value guarantee (see P0.14)

**Outputs:** intros/perks/resources/invites/check-ins \+ message drafts.

---

### **P0.11 Intro Engine 1.0 (3-intro fast start \+ ongoing intros)**

**What:** new member gets 3 intro recommendations; ongoing matchmaker engine.  
**Outputs:** intro suggestions with “why” and evidence; CM send flows.  
**Acceptance:** intro recommendations are grounded (goal/bottleneck/stack/location).

---

### **P0.12 Intro Outcome Tracking (mandatory learning loop)**

**What:** every intro has an outcome request:

* 1–10 rating  
* if \<6: required short feedback (text or audio)  
* escalation to CM if negative sentiment is detected

**Acceptance:** outcomes are logged; low ratings trigger root-cause tags.

---

### **P0.13 Perks Concierge 1.0 (Proactive \+ outcome feedback)**

**What:** match perks to member stack and needs; proactively recommend.  
**Inputs:** intake stack fields \+ perk DB.  
**Outputs:** perk DM drafts \+ perk send log; 1–10 rating with feedback \<6.  
**Acceptance:** perks are explainable (“because you use X”); CM can throttle per member if needed.

---

### **P0.14 Weekly Forced-Success Engine (value guarantee)**

**What:** scheduler that ensures each member receives at least one value drop per week.  
**Preference order (locked):**

1. intro  
2. perk  
3. resource  
4. workshop invite  
5. check-in question

**Output:** weekly queue of “best next value drops,” ranked by impact.

**Acceptance:** dashboard shows:

* due this week  
* already delivered this week  
* blocked by conversation state (see P0.15)

---

### **P0.15 Conversation-Aware Messaging Orchestrator (drafts \+ auto-send rules)**

**What:** system that drafts messages and sends them safely.

**Auto-send rule (locked):**

* auto-send only if:  
  * member replied to last CM message OR conversation marked “closed,” AND  
  * 24+ hours since last message

**No max frequency:** engagement-driven; prevents double-send.

**Outputs:**

* Draft queue with impact score  
* send decision: auto-send eligible vs manual review required  
* “merge drafts” suggestion if multiple opportunities exist

**Acceptance:** no automated double-sends; full audit log of sent messages.

---

### **P0.16 Mastermind System Intelligence (grouping \+ agenda intersections)**

**What:** support for the mastermind model described in the club doc.

* create/maintain mastermind groups (\~5 members)  
* suggest intersection topics based on members’ goals/bottlenecks  
* generate agendas

**Acceptance:** for each mastermind group, AI produces:

* 3–5 suggested agenda items  
* “who should lead next” rotation recommendation  
* follow-up action items per member after the call

---

### **P0.17 Mastermind Agenda Generator (monthly club-wide)**

Explicit requirement from B2B CMO Club AI starter doc.  
**What:** monthly agenda template “what’s most important to everyone in the club.”  
**Outputs:** agenda template \+ top themes \+ recommended speakers/workshops.

---

### **P0.18 Programming Planner 1.0 (workshops 2–4/month)**

**What:** data-driven planner to pick topics and candidate speakers.  
**Inputs:** Slack ask trends \+ mastermind themes \+ intake bottlenecks.  
**Outputs:** ranked topics \+ recommended internal speakers (from expertise proofs/wins).  
**Acceptance:** generates 2–4 suggested workshop topics/month with rationale.

---

### **P0.19 Perks Partner Pipeline Automation (perks campaign → hub)**

From B2B doc: perks campaign intake/acceptance → auto-add to perks hub \+ Slack feed.  
**What:** partner application pipeline \+ auto publish.  
**Outputs:** perk records, Slack \#perks announcement entries.  
**Acceptance:** no manual copy/paste; perk hub stays current.

---

### **P0.20 Internal AI Chat (dashboard)**

**What:** a chat interface for CM/founders to query the system.  
**Acceptance:** answers cite evidence and can generate action drafts.

---

