## **7\) Dashboard spec (what the CM actually uses)**

### **7.1 Member profile view (core page)**

Must include:

* Company snapshot (industry, revenue band, growth stage)  
* Personal goals (calls \+ Slack \+ surveys)  
* Current bottlenecks (Slack \+ calls)  
* Emotional state trend  
* Engagement velocity / churn trend  
* Stack \+ categories  
* Hiring plans  
* Latest signals (Slack \+ LinkedIn \+ careers \+ calls)  
* Suggested actions (ranked)  
* Draft messages (ready to send / queued)  
* Interaction history (intros, perks, outcomes)

**Actions on page:**

* “Generate briefing”  
* “Generate DM”  
* “Send DM” / “Approve auto-send”  
* “Create intro”  
* “Send perk”  
* “Mark conversation closed”  
* “Log outcome / request outcome”

### **7.2 Who Needs Attention (weekly)**

* ranked list  
* reason  
* playbook  
* one-click draft

### **7.3 Opportunity feed (real-time-ish)**

* filter by source: Slack / LinkedIn / careers / calls / surveys  
* filter by type: hiring / pain / win / topic trend / perk opportunity

### **7.4 Drafts queue**

* impact score  
* auto-send eligible flag  
* merge suggestions (avoid multiple messages about similar events)

### **7.5 Forced-success weekly queue**

* due this week  
* recommended action  
* blocked vs eligible

### **7.6 Intros queue \+ outcomes**

* pending intros  
* requested outcomes  
* low-score escalations

### **7.7 Perks queue \+ outcomes**

* recommended perks by member  
* redemption feedback  
* low-score escalations

### **7.8 Programming planner**

* mastermind intersection topics  
* workshop topics  
* speaker candidates

---

## **8\) Automation rules (locked)**

### **8.1 LinkedIn \+ careers refresh cadence**

* Every 12 hours per member:  
  * fetch public LinkedIn signals  
  * fetch careers page deltas  
  * run analysis summarization  
  * store summary \+ link \+ tags  
  * create opportunity items ranked by recency

### **8.2 Auto-send DM rules**

* Send if:  
  * (member replied after last outbound) OR (conversation closed)  
  * and 24h since last message  
* If not eligible:  
  * hold draft in queue for CM review

### **8.3 Weekly value guarantee**

* Every week per member:  
  * generate best action (intro \> perk \> resource \> invite \> check-in)  
  * queue as forced-success  
  * deliver automatically if eligible; otherwise highlight for CM

### **8.4 Outcome capture rules**

* Intro outcome: 1–10 rating  
* Perk outcome: 1–10 rating  
* Workshop outcome: 1–10 rating  
* If rating \< 6:  
  * require feedback (text or audio)  
  * run sentiment check; escalate to CM if negative

